definitions.definition: A surname from Middle English [in turn originating as a patronymic] meaning "son of Atkin ", a Middle English diminutive of Adam .

subdefinitions.definition: A number of places in the United States : A town and township in Henry County , Illinois . An unincorporated community in Center Township, Benton County , Indiana . An unincorporated township in Piscataquis County , Maine . A township in Carlton County , Minnesota . A city and township in Holt County , Nebraska . A town in Rockingham County , New Hampshire . A town in Pender County , North Carolina .
A community in Cumberland County , Nova Scotia , Canada .
A village in Saint Andrew parish, Dominica .

main_definition: A surname from Middle English [in turn originating as a patronymic] meaning "son of Atkin ", a Middle English diminutive of Adam .
